{"url": "https://people.com/royals/royal-wedding-prince-harry-picked-flowers-meghan-markle-bouquet/", "text": "Meghan Markle\u2018s bouquet had a very special touch: a few flowers handpicked by her husband.\n\nOn Friday, before heading to Windsor ahead of their wedding, Prince Harry picked several flowers from the couple\u2019s private garden at their home at Kensington Palace. He gave them to florist Philippa Craddock to be added to her bespoke bridal bouquet.\n\nDon\u2019t miss out! Tune in to Meghan and Harry \u2013 a Fairy-Tale Wedding on Saturday, May 19, starting at 6 a.m. ET/ 3 a.m. PT on PeopleTV \u2014 now available on PeopleTV.com and on your favorite streaming device.\n\nHer beautiful bouquet also had a tribute to Princess Diana, Harry\u2019s mother: the inclusion of Forget-Me-Nots, Diana\u2019s favorite flowers. According to the palace, the use of the Forget-Me-Nots was intentional to honor Diana\u2019s memory on the couple\u2019s wedding day.\n\nIt\u2019s the event of the year! Be sure to keep up with all of PEOPLE\u2019s royal wedding coverage and don\u2019t forget to check out everything you need to know about Meghan Markle\u2019s perfect style.\n\nThe wedding bouquet was done in the \u201cgentle, ethereal, relaxed\u201d style, according to a statement from the palace. A variety of flowers were included: scented sweet peas, lily of the valley, astilbe, jasmine and astrantia, and sprigs of myrtle all bound with a naturally dyed, raw silk ribbon.\n\nRELATED VIDEO: Meghan Markle: A Royal Like No Other\n\nThe sprigs of myrtle are a royal tradition. They come from stems in the gardens at Osborne House on the Isle of Wight, first planted by Queen Victoria in 1845. The sprigs in Meghan\u2019s bouquet come are from a plant grown from the same myrtle used in Queen Elizabeth\u2019s wedding bouquet in 1947.\n\nThe royal tradition of placing myrtle in a bridal bouquet dates back to Queen Victoria\u2019s reign. Prince Albert\u2019s grandmother gave Victoria a nosegay containing myrtle. That same year, Victoria purchased Osborne House and planted a spring on the grounds.\n\nQueen Victoria\u2019s eldest daughter, Princess Victoria, was the first to carry a spring of myrtle in her bouquet.", "images": ["https://people.com/thmb/ZvAhd1PP9kO8x1nmx6CeYcy_3YA=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Queen-Elizabeth-Prince-Philip-wedding-1-jpg-cbe332a4d2d0478eb4d1827f590aa3a4.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/EKlxP0gNpam0YcjHBNxV0IkpMUQ=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/prince-harry-serena-williams-meghan-markle-baby2baby-gala-west-hollywood-111025-d2d224a5d9a445b9839798ef38914e9d.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/k2MVcpPRLlF0coL7S6yFEwfocMw=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/prince-harry-meghan-markle-110725-bdaa13e8ec84464a88ae53b8344cbde0.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/26_J2fAXIKk0V705Qyb0Cs44ois=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/meghan-markle-prince-harry-1-111325-07ba1342d900451385e988735fb1cf84.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/ovFNjWLrSqBrPgcwAplysMT2Dak=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Meghan-Markle-attends-Fortune-Most-Powerful-Women-Summit-2025-meghan-markle-archie-lilibet-111825-77fa47a901cd40ff9ccc169af46c5fd9.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/R6D3o4sOuukxwrzvLh8DrNPzSKY=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Meghan-Markle-Prince-Harry-Kris-Jenner-110925-3-22ec68a7d8e440d5a6a73609cedb58d3.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/zNb84YLBb59-BPEl8qeAM9xtZvg=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/meghan-markle-prince-harry-111125-c76e9b31f1004d14b3a53adf53a51466.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/QIniS452eg1fVssrA_GWYzNyGGs=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Prince-Harry-Angela-Pearl-Meghan-Markle-111425-tout-d5c78c193a86445a85d2f7cdf806a2be.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/-QwBKSCLTgmjK3VYJ-XxtEQLjCU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal